object-type.Comment: allows us to figure out what operations should be done to repository objects during import and export

table.name: api_tokens
table.Comment: Records for the api tokens

table.name: asset_key_marker
table.Comment: Records are used to flag a particular record in the asset_key_meta_data table.

table.name: asset_key_meta_data
table.Comment: Each record holds meta data for an asset encryption key.

table.name: asset_list_items
table.Comment: Contains the individual list entries that correspond to the lists defined in the asset_lists table.

table.name: asset_lists
table.Comment: This table supports the creation of various types of per-user lists. The actual list contents are listed in the asset_list_items table.

table.name: async_jobs
table.Comment: Records information about background tasks that are run in response to some user action (as opposed to being run on some schedule).

table.name: authorizable_permission_sets
table.Comment: Many-to-many mapping table between authorizables and permission sets. An authorizable may have a permission set for every permission_set_class.

table.name: auto_saves
table.Comment: SUPPRESS_DOC_OUTPUT : Not currently used.

table.name: background_jobs
table.Comment: Records information about background tasks that are run by a Backgrounder process. These tasks are almost always run according to some schedule, but in a few cases they may also be triggered by some user actions.

table.name: background_jobs_cancel
table.Comment: BG jobs for which cancellation has been requested

table.name: big_texts
table.Comment: This table serves as a convenient place to store a big text object, if necessary. It's kind of a utility table. This table is really just used for internal purposes.

table.name: capabilities
table.Comment: Holds a relatively short list of capabilities. A user can be allowed certain capabilities either through being some sort of admin, or through owning something like a workbook or a project, or via entries in the next_gen_permissions table. Capabilities are things like read, write, export_data, publish, web_authoring, etc.

table.name: capability_roles
table.Comment: This table serves primarily to associate roles with capabilities. A given role can have many capabilities, and a given capability can be associated with several roles.

table.name: column_assets
table.Comment: Each record represents a column asset that exists on Tableau Server.

table.name: comment_attachments
table.Comment: Attachments for comments.

table.name: comments
table.Comment: Comments users made on views.

table.name: content_sync_token
table.Comment: Each record stores the checksum associated to a piece of content

table.name: core_licenses
table.Comment: SUPPRESS_DOC_OUTPUT

table.name: customized_views
table.Comment: When a user creates a customized view, the data that supports that goes in this table.

table.name: data_alerts
table.Comment: Each record represents an alert. An alert is a predefined data conditions on a view, and if conditions are met all alert recipients get notified.

table.name: data_alerts_recipients
table.Comment: Each record represents the intent of recipient to be notified if an event is triggered.

table.name: data_connections
table.Comment: Describes various data sources that are included in either workbooks or datasources.

table.name: data_quality_indicators
table.Comment: Table to store data quality indicators.

table.name: data_role_contents_association
table.Comment: Represents the association between the data_role and other content types.

table.name: data_roles
table.Comment: Each record represents an entry of Semantics Service data role metadata.

table.name: database_asset_events
table.Comment: Used to store database_asset events stream.

table.name: database_assets
table.Comment: Each record represents a database that exists on Tableau Server.

table.name: dataengine_configurations
table.Comment: SUPPRESS_DOC_OUTPUT

table.name: datasource_events
table.Comment: Used to store datasource events stream.

table.name: datasource_fields
table.Comment: Describes datasource fields.

table.name: datasource_metrics_aggregations
table.Comment: Each record represents a partial aggregation of analytics for a given datasource in a given time interval. It is often necessary to sum across multiple rows to find a total for a given time interval.

table.name: datasource_refresh_properties
table.Comment: Extension of datasources table for refresh properties (Online). This is 1-0/1 relationship to datasources table. It is a separate table since it contains Online-specific properties.

table.name: datasource_remote_query_agent
table.Comment: SUPPRESS_DOC_OUTPUT

table.name: datasource_versions
table.Comment: Datasource versions saved on server.

table.name: datasources
